news.title: U.S. inflation rises 0.1% in May from prior month, less than expected
news.summary: Consumer price index expected to rise 0.2% in May. 12-month inflation rate expected to be 2.4% for May.

news.title: JPMorgan's Jamie Dimon warns U.S. economy could soon 'deteriorate'
news.summary: "Hopefully, it's just a little bit," Dimon says of the economy. "Employment will come down a little. Inflation will go up," he says.

news.title: Trump says China will supply rare earths in 'done' deal
news.summary: U.S. President Donald Trump said magnets and "any necessary rare earths" will be supplied up front by China as part of a trade agreement.

news.title: Elon Musk says he regrets some social media posts he made about Trump
news.summary: Elon Musk said he regretted some of the social media posts he made last week. Musk was involved in an explosive public dispute with U.S. President Donald Trump.

news.title: Nvidia CEO says quantum computing is reaching an 'inflection point'
news.summary: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang says quantum computing is reaching an inflection point. He says it will start to solve real-world problems in the coming years.

news.title: Congress is playing havoc with your investments. Here’s how to beat Washington’s game.
news.summary: Expect lawmakers to punt decisions and own stock in companies with top government-affairs teams that know the system. Expect lawmakers to own shares in companies that know how to get things done in Washington.

news.title: Here’s how the 55% U.S. tariffs on China are broken down
news.summary: The U.S. is “getting a total of 55% tariffs,” Trump said in a post on Truth Social. Trump said the tariffs will go into effect on January 1, 2018.

news.title: Chewy’s stock slides as a dip in profitability disappoints investors with high expectations
news.summary: Chewy Inc. took a hit to gross margin in its first-quarter results. The results came as a surprise to investors, who have been growing more optimistic.

news.title: Inflation still not showing tariff-related spike, CPI shows. Muted prices open path for Fed rate cuts later in the year.
news.summary: Consumer prices showed little sign of tariff-related increases for the third month in a row. This defies expectations of a significant rise in inflation tied to ongoing U.S. trade wars.

news.title: Why Goldman Sachs says high-flying tech stocks may be headed for a tough stretch
news.summary: Goldman Sachs: Tech stocks might just be starting to lose some of their recent steam. The market is headed toward a tougher period, says Goldman Sachs specialist.
